                                  key="n50003087"
                                  type="alt">Muhammad Qāsim "Firishtah",<foreign xml:lang="fa">محمد قاسم فرشته</foreign>
                        </persName>, who brought his narrative down to<date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" notBefore="1606" notAfter="1607">1015</date>
                     </note>
                     <note>This glossary was compiled for<persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/95315274"
                                  key="n88125326"
                                  xml:lang="en"
                                  type="standard">John Briggs</persName>, the celebrated editor and translator of<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ferishtah</title>, by<persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Khairāt ʻAlī Khān “Mushtāq”,<foreign xml:lang="fa">خیرات علی خان مشتاق</foreign>
                        </persName>in<date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" notBefore="1825" notAfter="1826">1241</date>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Arberry 1939, page 354.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
